== 2-Way Checkback

@ ON after both minors or both majors
@ ON vs take-out double by either opp +
@ #OFF if either opp has shown a suit#
@@ cue = GF, jumps are inv +

*Passed hand*
@ 2C{thinsp}{forces}{thinsp}2D ON
@ 2D = natural weak, 5*M

=== Inv with both majors

Rev. Flannery on the 1st-round takes care of weak hands with 5*{S} and
4{or}5*{H}.  So we have an extra sequence to show inv both majors.

A direct bid of the 2nd major shows equal length.

[%autowidth,cols="3*^,<",grid="none"]
|===
| 1m  | 1H | |
| 1NT | 2S | | 4*{S}, 4*{H}, inv
|===

[%autowidth,cols="3*^,<",grid="none"]
|===
| 1m  | 1S | |
| 1NT | 2H | | 5*{S}, 5*{H}, inv
|===

Going though the minor-suit relay shows unequal length.

[%autowidth,cols="3*^,<",grid="none"]
|===
| 1m   | 1H   | |
| 1NT  | !2C! | |
| !2D! | 2S   | | 4*{S}, 5*{H}, inv
|===

[%autowidth,cols="3*^,<",grid="none"]
|===
| 1m   | 1S   | |
| 1NT  | !2C! | |
| !2D! | 2H   | | 5*{S}, 4*{H}, inv
|===

